<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE recipe SYSTEM "../recipes.dtd">
<recipe>
	<title>Holland Cream</title>
	<meta>
        <source>http://allrecipes.com/recipe/holland-cream-white-cream-filling/</source>
		<dishtype>Fillings</dishtype>
		<comment>This is the white creme filling in donuts. I love it with a chocolate icing. I don't know where the name comes from, but the recipes online, which all seem to be copies of each other, all call it that.</comment>
	</meta>
	<ingredients>
		<ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>225</value>
                <unit>g</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>1</value>
                        <unit>cup</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
            </quantity>
			<item>sugar</item>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>100</value>
                <unit>g</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>1/2</value>
                        <unit>cup</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
            </quantity>
			<item>water</item>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>
				<value>200</value>
				<unit>g</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>1</value>
                        <unit>cup</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
			</quantity>
			<item>vegetable oil</item>
		</ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>
				<value>360</value>
				<unit>g</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>2</value>
                        <unit>cups</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
			</quantity>
			<item>vegetable shortening</item>
		</ingredient>
        <ingredient>
            <quantity>
                <value>1</value>
                <unit>tsp</unit>
            </quantity>
            <item>clear vanilla extract</item>
        </ingredient>
		<ingredient>
			<quantity>
				<value>1</value>
				<unit>kg</unit>
                <altmeasure>
                    <quantity>
                        <value>8</value>
                        <unit>cups</unit>
                    </quantity>
                </altmeasure>
			</quantity>
			<item>confectioners' sugar</item>
		</ingredient>
	</ingredients>
	<steps>
		<step>Put the white sugar and water in a <equipment>saucepan</equipment>. Put on medium heat and bring to a boil, stirring until the sugar has dissolved.</step>
		<step>Remove from heat, pour the syrup into a large mixing bowl, and let cool completely.</step>
		<step>Add vegetable oil, shortening, and clear vanilla extract, and beat with an electric mixer on high speed to blend.</step>
		<step>Add the confectioners' sugar 1 cup at a time and beat in. Continue to beat until the filling is thick and fluffy. If it's too thick, beat in a tablespoon of water at a time until it's the correct consistency.</step>
	</steps>
</recipe>
